# Multi-Phase Plan Convergence

When the user **approves** a spec or implementation plan, **do not write production code yet**. First decompose into phased subplans, run a **plan-level** convergence pass, then execute phases sequentially with **implementation-level** convergence on every task.

Works with `subagent-driven-development`, `fix-review-before-stack`, `review-evidence-discipline`, `design-intent-debate-before-change`, `test-before-report`, and the **review-bugbot** skill.

---

## Convergence gate (read first — mandatory)

**Implementation is not done when code is written.** Every agent must run the mistake convergence loop (`fix-review-before-stack`) at these gates — **before** advancing:

```
Task done     → 2× Pass 2→3 on task diff     → then next task
Phase done    → 2× Pass 2→3 on phase diff    → then phase N+1
Step module   → 2× Pass 2→3 on step diff      → then wire next step
All phases    → 3× Program Pass 2→3           → then report plan complete
```

**Invalid transitions (forbidden):**
- pytest passed once → start next phase
- todos marked complete → skip convergence
- Bugbot findings fixed → report done without Pass 2→3 on the **fix** diff
- "Will run convergence later" → start unrelated work or next phase

If you cannot cite convergence round counts + verification exit codes from **this session**, you are **not** allowed to say the task, phase, or plan is complete.

---

## Trigger

User says **approved**, **implement the plan**, **LGTM**, or equivalent after reviewing a spec/plan draft.

Until subplans exist and pass the plan gate below → **planning mode only**.

---

## Step 1 — Master index plan (required)

Create `docs/superpowers/plans/YYYY-MM-DD-<feature>-index.md` (or extend an existing index).

**Must include:**

| Section | Content |
|---------|---------|
| Goal | One sentence |
| Phase map | Table: phase #, subplan file, **type**, depends-on, status |
| Global constraints | Verbatim from approved spec — copied once, inherited by all phases |
| Verification protocol | Convergence loop (see below) |
| Execution order | Sequential phases; optional phases marked |
| Success criteria | Program-level, testable |

**Phase types** (label every subplan):

| Type | When to use |
|------|-------------|
| `implement` | New behavior per design |
| `refactor` | Restructure without behavior change (or with explicit parity tests) |
| `cleanup` | Remove dead code, flags, duplicates superseded by earlier phases |
| `migrate` | Move callers off deprecated APIs; delete only after migration gate |

One concern per phase. Do not mix unrelated subsystems in one subplan.

**Reference shape:** `docs/superpowers/plans/2026-07-23-openalgo-market-authority-index.md`

---

## Step 2 — One subplan per phase (required before any code)

Each phase → `docs/superpowers/plans/YYYY-MM-DD-<feature>-phase-N-<slug>.md`

Use `writing-plans` skill structure: file map, tasks with Files/Interfaces, checkbox steps, phase pytest scope, completion gate.

Each subplan header must state: **Type**, **Depends on**, **Supersedes** (if any), **Out of scope**.

---

## Step 3 — Plan-level convergence (before implementation)

Review the **plan set**, not code. Minimum one full round; repeat until no new CONFIRMED plan defects.

```
Plan Pass A — Decompose audit
  - Every approved spec requirement maps to exactly one phase (or explicit deferral)
  - Dependencies acyclic; no phase assumes work from a later phase
  - Cleanup/migrate phases exist where old paths must be removed
  - Global constraints copied verbatim; no drift between index and subplans

Plan Pass B — Edge cases & design flaws
  - Triple debate (design-intent-debate-before-change) on risky cuts: routing,
    authority, date boundaries, parallel code paths, status rollup, deprecation
  - Label findings: CONFIRMED GAP / BY DESIGN / HYPOTHESIS / DEFERRED
  - Fix plan text for CONFIRMED GAP; do not "fix in code" during planning

Plan Pass C — Adversarial plan review
  - Dispatch task reviewer or general reviewer subagent on index + all subplans
  - User may approve plan set explicitly, or implicit approval to proceed after fixes
```

**Plan gate:** All subplan files exist; phase map complete; Plan Pass C has zero open **CONFIRMED GAP** rows.

Only then announce implementation start and create SDD todos.

---

## Step 4 — Implementation (per phase, per task)

Follow `subagent-driven-development`:

1. Read **one phase subplan**; todos for all its tasks.
2. **One implementer subagent per task** (sequential within phase).
3. After **each task** — mandatory **implementation convergence loop** (see `fix-review-before-stack` **Mandatory checkpoints** — **2× Pass 2→3 minimum** on the task diff before the next task):

**You may not mark a task complete or start the next task until** convergence rounds are cited with verification exit codes from **this session**.

```
Task Pass 0 — Research + label (CONFIRMED / HYPOTHESIS / BY DESIGN / UNKNOWN)
Task Pass 1 — Implement smallest change; symmetry grep parallel paths
Task Pass 2 — Author audit: git diff line-by-line + full scoped verification
Task Pass 3 — Adversarial review: Bugbot subagent (review-bugbot skill,
              Diff: uncommitted changes) OR manual mistake checklist from
              fix-review-before-stack
Task Pass 4 — Fix CONFIRMED / user-approved items → Task Pass 2 on NEW diff
```

**Stop task when:** ≥2 full Task Pass 2→3 cycles **and** 0 new **CONFIRMED** on latest diff **and** verification exit 0 this session.

**Phase completion gate:** After all tasks in a phase, run **one additional** 2× Pass 2→3 cycle on the **combined phase diff** before starting phase N+1. Cite round counts in the phase summary.

---

## Step 5 — Program completion gate (MANDATORY — no exceptions)

When **all phases/tasks** in an approved plan are implemented, the **very next step** before reporting plan complete, committing final work, or starting unrelated tasks is the **program-level mistakes convergence loop**. Skipping this invalidates the plan completion claim.

```
Program Pass 2 — Full-plan author audit
  - git diff / git log for entire plan scope line-by-line
  - Full scoped verification suite (exit codes from this session)
  - Symmetry grep: parallel paths introduced by the plan (API vs batch, session vs agent, list vs live)

Program Pass 3 — Adversarial review (Bugbot on plan diff OR manual mistake checklist)
  - Label every finding CONFIRMED / HYPOTHESIS / BY DESIGN / UNKNOWN
  - Re-read primary sources; subagent output is discovery only

Program Pass 4 — Fix CONFIRMED items → return to Program Pass 2 on NEW diff
```

**Stop program only when:**

1. **Minimum three full Program Pass 2→3 cycles** completed on the latest diff (not two — three is mandatory for plan completion).
2. **Zero new CONFIRMED** issues in plan-touched code on the latest diff.
3. Verification commands cited from **this session** with exit codes.

**Report format (required in final plan summary):**

`Program convergence round 1: N CONFIRMED → fixed` / `round 2: …` / `round 3: Pass 3 — 0 new CONFIRMED`

**Forbidden after plan implementation:**

- Reporting "plan done" or "all todos complete" without program convergence rounds cited
- Moving to the next plan or unrelated work with open CONFIRMED rows from Program Pass 3
- Single-pass Bugbot or self-review only
- Citing verification from a prior session

Works with `fix-review-before-stack` (task-level loops) — program gate runs **after** all task/phase gates pass, on the **combined plan diff**.

---

## Bugbot invocation (implementation Pass 3)

```text
Full Repository Path: <repo absolute path>
Diff: uncommitted changes
Custom Instructions: <phase-specific regressions: silent failures, wrong-frame routing,
  asymmetric paths, status rollup, migration leftovers>
```

Re-read every Bugbot finding in primary sources before labeling CONFIRMED.

---

## Reporting (mandatory)

**After plan gate:**

- List subplan paths and phase types
- Note any DEFERRED / HYPOTHESIS items

**After each phase:**

- Convergence round counts (`Phase 2 round 1: 1 CONFIRMED → fixed; round 2: 0 CONFIRMED`)
- Verification commands + exit codes from **this session**
- Separate CONFIRMED fixed vs HYPOTHESIS deferred vs BY DESIGN

---

## Forbidden

- Starting implementation before index + all required subplans exist
- Skipping plan-level convergence on multi-phase work
- Single-pass review before marking a task or phase done
- **Reporting plan complete or closing plan todos without Step 5 program convergence (minimum three rounds)**
- Parallel implementer subagents on the same phase
- Mixing cleanup/migration into an implement phase without an explicit migration gate task
- Reporting "done" without fresh verification exit codes
- **Starting phase N+1 while phase N convergence rounds are uncited or incomplete**

---

## When to skip full decomposition

Single-file, single-task fix with no spec → use `targeted-bug-fix-discipline` + `fix-review-before-stack` only; no index plan required.

If approved scope spans **2+ subsystems**, **refactor + new behavior**, or **deprecation** → full multi-phase workflow is **required**.
